			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Updated x86-64 validator to recognize correct arguments for the string instructions, and to recognize multiple segment address dependencies within a single instruction.

Added restriction that one must use mov (on the corresponding 32-bit register) to compute the segment addresses. Hence, the allowable pattern for string instructions is:

mov %esi, %esi
lea (%r15, %rsi), %rsi
mov %esi, %edi
lea (%r15, %rdi), %rdi
movsb %ds:(%rsi), %es:(%rdi)
</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-01-20T18:49:31.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-01-20T18:49:31.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 12 by kschi...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2532#c12" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2532/comments/full/12" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>